'''Cytology''' (from Greek , ''kytos'', "a hollow"; and , ''-logia'') is the study of cells. Cytology is that branch of life science that deals with the study of cells in terms of structure, function and chemistry. Robert Hooke is sometimes seen as the father of cytology.Bill Nye (host), the 100 greatest discoveries: biology, Documentary by DiscoveryBased on usage it can refer to:*Cytopathology: the study of ''cellular'' disease and the use of cellular changes for the diagnosis of disease.*Cell biology: the study of (normal) cellular anatomy, function and chemistry.The International Academy of Cytology has as its official journal ''Acta Cytologica''.See also* Cytopathology* Liver cytologyReferencesast:Citoloxíagl:Citoloxíamk:Клеточна биологијаur:خلوی حیاتیات